# MCP Route Handlers & Tools

Flashycardy exposes **Streamable HTTP MCP** at **`/api/mcp`** (Clerk OAuth + session JWT fallback). Every **public REST** operation under `src/app/api/` (except `mcp/`) must have a **matching MCP tool**.

REST conventions: **`api-route-handlers.mdc`**, **`public-api.mdc`**. Docs: `apps/docs/content/api/mcp/overview.mdx`, `apps/docs/content/developers/mcp-architecture.mdx`.

## Layout

```
src/app/.well-known/
  oauth-protected-resource/mcp/route.ts   # protectedResourceHandlerClerk
  oauth-authorization-server/route.ts     # authServerMetadataHandlerClerk

src/app/api/mcp/route.ts                  # createMcpHandler + withMcpAuth(verifyMcpToken)

src/lib/mcp/
  verify-mcp-token.ts    # OAuth verifyClerkToken → session fallback → AuthInfo.extra
  register-tools.ts      # server.registerTool for each REST operation
  tools/<verb>-<resource>.ts
  extra.ts, tool-context.ts, tool-result.ts, pagination-args.ts, constants.ts
```

- **Local client URL:** `http://localhost:3000/api/mcp` (`http://`, not `https://`, unless local TLS).
- **Do not** add `withAuth`, CORS, or `OPTIONS` on `api/mcp/route.ts`.
- **Clerk Dashboard:** OAuth app + dynamic client registration when clients require it.

## Auth (`verify-mcp-token.ts`)

1. **OAuth (preferred):** `auth({ acceptsToken: "oauth_token" })` + `verifyClerkToken` from `@clerk/mcp-tools/next`.
2. **Fallback:** `authenticateRequest(req, { acceptsToken: "session_token" })`.

Populates **`AuthInfo.extra`:** `{ userId, hasUnlimitedDecks }` for tools. Billing must match REST (`unlimited_decks` feature).

## `api/mcp/route.ts`

- `withMcpAuth(mcpCore, verifyMcpToken, { required: true, resourceMetadataPath: "/.well-known/oauth-protected-resource/mcp" })`
- Export **GET**, **POST**, **DELETE**; `disableSse: true`; `maxDuration = 60`

## REST ↔ MCP parity (required)

| REST | MCP tool |
|------|----------|
| `GET` collection | `list_<resource>` |
| `GET` one / count | `get_<resource>` / `get_<resource>_count` |
| `POST` | `create_<resource>` |
| `PUT` | `replace_<resource>` |
| `PATCH` | `patch_<resource>` |
| `DELETE` | `delete_<resource>` |

When adding or changing **`src/app/api/**/route.ts`**:

1. **`src/lib/mcp/tools/<verb>-<resource>.ts`** — export Zod `*InputSchema` + `run*(ctx: McpToolContext, input)` using **`@/db/queries/*`** (same as REST).
2. **`register-tools.ts`** — `server.registerTool("name", { title, description, inputSchema }, handler)`; description cites REST path.
3. **Handler:** `parseMcpAuthExtra(extra.authInfo)` → `mcpToolError("Unauthorized")` if null → `run*(ctx, args)`.
4. **Pagination lists:** `pageFieldsSchema`, `parsePageArgs`, `paginationMeta` (`pagination-args.ts`).
5. **Plan limits:** `ctx.hasUnlimitedDecks` + `FREE_DECK_LIMIT` (`constants.ts`).
6. **Tests:** `tools/<name>.test.ts` (mock queries). **Docs:** `apps/docs/content/api/mcp/overview.mdx` + `apps/docs/content/api/rest-api.mdx` (or per-endpoint pages under `api/endpoints/`).

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD — tool mirrors REST validation and queries
export async function runCreateDeck(ctx: McpToolContext, input: CreateDeckInput) {
  if (!ctx.hasUnlimitedDecks && (await getDeckCountByUser(ctx.userId)) >= FREE_DECK_LIMIT) {
    return mcpToolError("Deck limit reached for the free plan");
  }
  return mcpJsonContent({ data: deck });
}

// ❌ BAD — new REST route with no register-tools entry
// ❌ BAD — inline Drizzle in MCP tool or different Zod limits than REST
```

## MCP responses

- Success: **`mcpJsonContent({ data, meta? })`** — JSON in `content[0].text`.
- Error: **`mcpToolError("message")`** (`isError: true`) — reuse REST error strings when possible.

## Rules

- One MCP tool per public REST method; keep parity table in docs updated.
- Tools use **`McpToolContext`**, not `auth()` directly.
- Business logic only in **`src/db/queries/*`** — shared with REST routes.
- Metadata only via **`@clerk/mcp-tools`** on `.well-known` — no manual `CLERK_OAUTH_ISSUER` routes unless Clerk requires it.
